    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
                 throws ImplerException
        Starts Implementor with arguments. If number of args is two, create implementation of given interface and put it to given path. If number of args is three, create implementation of given interface, pack it in .jar file and put it to given path.
        Parameters:
        args - arguments from command line
        Throws:
        info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.
        ImplerException

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        Makes implementation of the given interface , compile it and make jar-file of the compiled implementation.
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        jarFile - directory where .jar should be placed to
        Throws:
        info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - if arguments are wrong/compilation finish with error or can't create .jar file in given directory
        ImplerException

      • implement

        public void implement(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Creates a file that implements interface. Output file contains java class, that implements given interface and compiles without errors. The output file is in the same package which is the source interface. Interface must not contain generics.
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.
        ImplerException
